# ROVEXO v1.0 — Final Release Protection

**STATUS: APPROVED | PROTECTED | PERMANENT**

Live deployment is fail-closed. It is allowed only when every required check
passes and the calculated certification score is exactly 100%.

Required gates: UI, UX, Auth, Homepage, Orders, Checkout, Wallet, Tracking,
Notifications, Messages, Reviews, Performance, Responsive, Database,
Migrations, Full Demo, Buyer flow, Seller flow, Playwright, TypeScript, ESLint,
production build, and all protected contracts.

Rules:
- One failed, missing, skipped, pending, unavailable, or unverifiable check
  blocks deployment.
- Scores from 0–99.999% always block deployment.
- Never use thresholds, averages, synthetic defaults, or static file presence
  as substitutes for required runtime evidence.
- Never bypass, weaken, delete, reset, or convert a required gate to advisory.
- No manual overrides by Super Admin, Product Owner, Staff, Developers,
  Deployment Center, Vercel, CI/CD, or Release Actions.
- Deployment actions and Vercel builds must execute the canonical predeploy
  certification and exit non-zero on any failure.
